claim.claim-text:
1. A double-hung window assembly having an opening defined by a head jamb, a first side jamb, a second side jamb and a sill, wherein the double-hung window assembly comprises:
each of the first and second side jambs comprising an upper side jamb, a lower side jamb, an interior extension slot, an exterior extension slot and a lock pin slot;
an upper sash held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second upper side jambs and head jamb when the upper sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly;
a lower sash having a lock pin extendable from each side of the lower sash into the lock pin slot of its respective side jamb, the lower sash held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second lower side jambs and sill when the lower sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly;
a concealed jamb liner cover for selective engagement with each upper side jamb, each jamb liner cover extending over the interior extension slot and lock pin slot at its respective upper side jamb, and each jamb liner cover having an exposed wood surface and having a channel receiving the lock pin of the lower sash, allowing slidable movement of the lower sash.

12. A double-hung window assembly having an opening defined by a head jamb, a first side jamb, a second side jamb and a sill, wherein the window assembly has a uniform interior wood appearance, and wherein the double-hung window comprises:
each of the first and second side jambs having an upper side jamb and a lower side jamb;
an upper sash having a wood frame, the upper sash being held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second upper side jambs and head jamb when the upper sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly;
a lower sash having a wood frame and a lock pin extendable from each side of the lower sash, the lower sash being held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second lower side jambs and sill when the lower sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly;
a concealed jamb liner cover for selective engagement with each upper side jamb, each jamb liner cover having an exposed wood surface and having a channel receiving the lock pin of the lower sash, allowing slidable movement of the lower sash;
an upper sash lock housing attached to an upper portion of the wood frame of the upper sash, wherein the upper sash lock housing holds an upper sash lock pin for each side of the upper sash; and
a wooden interior upper parting stop connected to the head jamb having a length sufficient to conceal the upper sash lock housing when the upper sash in its closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly.

18. A double-hung window assembly having an opening defined by a head iamb, a first side jamb, a second side jamb and a sill, wherein the double-hung window assembly comprises:
each of the first and second side jambs comprising an upper side jamb and a lower side jamb;
an upper sash having a frame with a first surface finish appearance on an interior side thereof, the upper sash being held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second upper side jambs when the upper sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly;
a lower sash having a frame with the first surface finish appearance on an interior side thereof, and having a lock pin extendable from each side of the lower sash, the lower sash being held in the opening of the window assembly by the first and second lower side jambs when the lower sash is in a closed position relative to the opening of the window assembly; and
a concealed jamb liner cover for selective engagement with each upper side jamb, each jamb liner cover having an exposed surface with the first surface finish appearance thereon and having a channel receiving the lock pin of the lower sash, allowing slidable movement of the lower sash.
